The methods’ performances are estimated by considering that a period of 4 consecutive days is classified as pre-exacerbation if it includes at least a given number of atypical days. In Fig. 3, the ROC curves for each case are presented. Table 2 gives the corresponding performances concerning the average AUC and its standard deviation.Fig. 3
